SIMPLE: riddle
RECORDS: 5

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Riddle
<hw>Rid"dle</hw> <pr>(r⟦icr⟧d"d'l)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>ridil</ets>, AS. <ets>hridder</ets>; akin to G. <ets>reiter</ets>,
L. <ets>cribrum</ets>, and to Gr. <grk>kri`nein</grk> to distinguish,
separate, and G. <ets>rein</ets> clean. See <er>Crisis</er>,
<er>Certain</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A sieve with coarse meshes,
usually of wire, for separating coarser materials from finer, as chaff
from grain, cinders from ashes, or gravel from sand.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A board having a row of pins, set zigzag, between
which wire is drawn to straighten it.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Riddle</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Riddle
<hw>Rid"dle</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Riddled</conjf> <pr>(r⟦icr⟧d"d'ld)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Riddling</conjf> <pr>(r⟦icr⟧d"dl⟦icr⟧ng)</pr>.]</vmorph>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>To separate, as grain from the chaff, with a riddle; to
pass through a riddle; <as>as, <ex>riddle</ex> wheat; to <ex>riddle</ex>
coal or gravel</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To perforate so as to make like a riddle; to make
many holes in; <as>as, a house <ex>riddled</ex> with
shot</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Riddle</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Riddle
<hw>Rid"dle</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[For <ets>riddels</ets>, <it>s</it>
being misunderstood as the plural ending; OE. <ets>ridels</ets>,
<ets>redels</ets>. AS. r⟦aemac⟧dels; akin to D. <ets>raadsel</ets>, G.
<ets>r⟦aum⟧thsel</ets>; fr. AS. <ets>r⟦aemac⟧dan</ets> to counsel or
advise, also, to guess. ⟦root⟧116. Cf. <er>Read</er>.]</ety>
<def>Something proposed to be solved by guessing or conjecture; a
puzzling question; an ambiguous proposition; an enigma; hence, anything
ambiguous or puzzling.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>To wring from me, and tell to them, my secret,⟦br⟧
That solved the <qex>riddle</qex> which I had proposed.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>'T was a strange <qex>riddle</qex> of a lady.</q>
<rj><qau>Hudibras.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Riddle</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 4 ====
HEADWORD: Riddle
<hw>Rid"dle</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To explain; to solve; to
unriddle.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Riddle</qex> me this, and guess him if you can.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Riddle</ent>⟦br⟧

